<pre>?ERROR</pre>

<p>
Welcome to $SITE.
The links at the top and bottom of the page will help you to manage the
$DOMAIN domain.  You can return to this introduction at any time by
pressing <b>Help</b>.
</p>

<table cellspacing="15" width="100%">
<tr>
  <td valign="top">Sign In
  </td>
  <td>

If you finish administering the $LIST list and wish to change
to another list, press <b>Sign In</b>.  You will be prompted
for a new mailing list name and password.  Your temporary password 
for this session will continue to be valid.

  </td>
</tr>
<tr>
  <td valign="top">Sign Out
  </td>
  <td>

If you finish administering the $LIST list and wish to end
this session, press <b>Sign Out</b>.  Your temporary password
for this session will be invalidated.

  </td>
</tr>
<tr>
  <td valign="top">Moderation
  </td>
  <td>

Occasionally, posted messages, subscriptions, and other requests
will need your approval before they are completed.  Press 
<b>Moderation</b> to see all of the unfinished requests for every
mailing list at $SITE. 
The requests labeled <b>consult</b> await the approval of an
administrator, whereas the requests labeled <b>confirm</b> await the
approval of the people who made them.  The requests labeled <b>delay</b>
will be completed automatically at a later time.

  </td>
</tr>
<tr>
  <td valign="top">Registry
  </td>
  <td>

Press <b>Registry</b> to see the first 20 e-mail addresses of
people who have registered at $SITE.  
Whenever someone joins a mailing list, the e-mail address of that person
is registered automatically.  

  </td>
</tr>
<tr>
  <td valign="top">Configuration
  </td>
  <td>

Majordomo has over 100 GLOBAL configuration settings which you can
use to fine-tune the performance of your domain.  To manage them 
more easily, they have been divided into several categories.
Press <b>Configuration</b> to see a list of these categories.
You can then view and change the current settings.

  </td>
</tr>
<tr>
  <td valign="top">Defaults
  </td>
  <td>

Majordomo has over 100 DEFAULT configuration settings which you can
use to set the default values for every mailing list in this domain.  
To manage them more easily, they have been divided into several 
categories.  Press <b>Defaults</b> to see a list of these categories.
You can then view and change the current settings.

  </td>
</tr>
<tr>
  <td valign="top">Create Lists
  </td>
  <td>

If you wish to create, rename, or destroy a mailing list, press 
<b>Create Lists</b>.
  </td>
</tr>
<tr>
  <td valign="top">Command Form
  </td>
  <td>

Although the other features of this WWW service will allow you
to perform many common tasks, not every task is supported yet.
However, the <b>Command Form</b> offers a primitive way of 
issuing commands that may be easier for experienced administrators.
<p>
In particular, the $HELP:GET, $HELP:INDEX, and $HELP:PUT
commands are supported only by the command form.

  </td>
</tr>
<tr>
  <td valign="top">Help
  </td>
  <td>

Majordomo has over 100 cross-referenced help documents.
They describe how to email commands to Majordomo at
<a href="mailto:$MJ">$MJ</a>.  
The help pages may be displayed in a new window in your web browser.

<p>
To see the help document for a particular topic, type its
name into the <b>Topic</b> box, then press the <b>help</b>
button.
</p>

<form method="POST" action="$CGIURL">
  <input type="hidden" name="user" value="$USER">
  <input type="hidden" name="passw" value="$CMDPASS">
  <input type="hidden" name="list" value="$LIST">
  <input type="hidden" name="func" value="help">
  Topic: 
  <input name="extra" value="">
  <input type="submit" name="f" value="help">
</form>

The following documents give a good introduction.
<dl>
  <dt>$HELP:ADMIN</dt>
    <dd>A basic introduction to list administration, including hints
    for solving common problems.</dd>

  <dt>$HELP:ADMIN_COMMANDS</dt>
    <dd>A summary of all of the commands available to list administrators.</dd>

  <dt>$HELP:ADMIN_DOMAIN</dt>
    <dd>A basic introduction to the administration of a domain, 
    such as $DOMAIN.</dd>

  <dt>$HELP:ADMIN_PASSWORDS (important!)</dt>
    <dd>How to use passwords when you email commands to Majordomo.</dd>

  <dt>$HELP:COMMANDS</dt>
    <dd>A summary of commands for list subscribers.</dd>

  <dt>$HELP:CONFIGSHOW</dt>
    <dd>How to see the current configuration settings for your list.</dd>

  <dt>$HELP:CONFIGSET and $HELP:CONFIGDEF</dt>
    <dd>How to change the configuration settings.</dd>

  <dt>$HELP:SET</dt>
    <dd>How to change the personal settings of your list's subscribers.</dd>

  <dt>$HELP:SUBSCRIBE</dt>
    <dd>How to add people to your mailing list.</dd>

  <dt>$HELP:UNSUBSCRIBE</dt>
    <dd>How to remove people from your mailing list.</dd>

  <dt>$HELP:SHOWTOKENS</dt>
    <dd>How to see a summary of requests that require moderation.</dd>

  <dt>$HELP:TOKENINFO</dt>
    <dd>How to obtain more information about one request that
        requires moderation.</dd>

  <dt>$HELP:WHO</dt>
    <dd>How to see who is subscribed to a mailing list.</dd>

  <dt>$HELP:MJ_WWWADM</dt>
    <dd>Technical details about this web interface.</dd>

</dl>
  </td>
</tr>
</table>
